# Git Workflow

## Branching

- **NEVER commit directly to `main`.**
- Always create a feature branch before making any code changes.
- Branch naming: `feature/<short-description>` or `fix/<short-description>`.

```bash
# ✅ CORRECT
git checkout -b feature/cv-item-scan
# ... make changes ...
git add -A && git commit -m "feat: ..."

# ❌ WRONG — committing directly to main
git add -A && git commit -m "feat: ..."   # while on main
```

## Commit messages

- Use conventional commits: `feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`, `refactor:`, `docs:`.
- One logical unit per commit.

## When to branch

- Every new feature → `feature/...`
- Every bug fix → `fix/...`
- Schema changes → `feature/...` (never directly on main)
